    {
      "id": 1,
      "text": "Ringoes, New Jersey, is the oldest known settlement in Hunterdon County, developing around John Ringo's Tavern on Old York Road, now Route 179.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        22
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ringoes%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The 187‑acre Ringoes Historic District was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1999 for its agricultural, architectural, and transportation heritage.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        25,
        30
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia",
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ringoes%2C_New_Jersey"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Ringoes' railroad station is one of the few surviving Hunterdon County examples and the only one still serving its original function.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.livingplaces.com/NJ/Hunterdon_County/East_Amwell_Township/Ringoes_Historic_District.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "Victorian homes in Ringoes blend Greek, Gothic, and Italianate styles, as seen in detailed houses like 20 and 41 John Ringo Road.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.livingplaces.com/NJ/Hunterdon_County/East_Amwell_Township/Ringoes_Historic_District.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Ringoes features the award‑winning Old York Cellars winery and the historic Amwell Valley Fire Station, adding to its charming small‑town aesthetic.",
